  <description>
    <p>In SuperCard, the <b>allowFieldRedraw</b> <glossary tag="property">property</glossary> determines whether scrolling <glossary tag="field">fields</glossary> are <glossary tag="redraw">redrawn</glossary> after scrolling. In LiveCode, scrolling <glossary tag="field">fields</glossary> are always <glossary tag="redraw">redrawn</glossary>.</p><p/><p>The <b>allowFieldRedraw</b> <glossary tag="property">property</glossary> is always set to false. A <glossary tag="handler">handler</glossary> can set it to any value without causing a <glossary tag="error">script error</glossary>, but the actual <function tag="value">value</function> is not changed.</p>
